      • isFilled

        public boolean isFilled()
        Determines if the field in question is empty or not. Used to determine if the field is ready for submission. A field is considered filled if under two conditions: first, if the field is required and the input text is deemed valid by the validator; or if the field is not a required field (input does not matter in this case).
        Specified by:
        isFilled in interface IField<T>
        Returns:
        True if the field is filled, false otherwise.
